#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:113
msgid "Configure the RDMA stack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:115
msgid ""
"Make sure your kernel configuration has RDMA support enabled. Under Device "
"Drivers -> InfiniBand support, update the kernel configuration to enable "
"InfiniBand support [NOTE: the option name is misleading. Enabling InfiniBand "
"support is required for all RDMA devices (IB, iWARP, etc.)]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:120
msgid ""
"Enable the appropriate IB HCA support (mlx4, mthca, ehca, ipath, etc.) or "
"iWARP adapter support (amso, cxgb3, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:123
msgid ""
"If you are using InfiniBand, be sure to enable IP-over-InfiniBand support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:125
msgid "Configure the NFS client and server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:127
msgid ""
"Your kernel configuration must also have NFS file system support and/or NFS "
"server support enabled. These and other NFS related configuration options "
"can be found under File Systems -> Network File Systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:131
msgid "Build, install, reboot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:133
msgid ""
"The NFS/RDMA code will be enabled automatically if NFS and RDMA are turned "
"on. The NFS/RDMA client and server are configured via the hidden "
"SUNRPC_XPRT_RDMA config option that depends on SUNRPC and INFINIBAND. The "
"value of SUNRPC_XPRT_RDMA will be:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:138
msgid ""
"N if either SUNRPC or INFINIBAND are N, in this case the NFS/RDMA client and "
"server will not be built"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:141
msgid ""
"M if both SUNRPC and INFINIBAND are on (M or Y) and at least one is M, in "
"this case the NFS/RDMA client and server will be built as modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:144
msgid ""
"Y if both SUNRPC and INFINIBAND are Y, in this case the NFS/RDMA client and "
"server will be built into the kernel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfs-rdma.rst:147
msgid ""
"Therefore, if you have followed the steps above and turned no NFS and RDMA, "
"the NFS/RDMA client and server will be built."
msgstr ""

